1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

This document summarizes the conceptual engineering work completed during the design phase for the Artificial Musculature Architecture (AMA-220).

The objective is to support the development of a modular artificial muscle system capable of integrating with a hydraulic robotic skeleton driven by the PI220 3VS3 Electro-Hydraulic Actuator Architecture.

The artificial musculature is intended to improve:

• Shock absorption
• Vibration damping
• Mechanical protection
• Motion smoothness
• Structural stability
• Fatigue resistance
• Maintainability

The primary structural loads remain supported by the mechanical skeleton and hydraulic actuation system.

All conclusions contained in this document represent conceptual engineering work intended to guide laboratory research and must be validated experimentally before engineering performance claims are established.

