2. PROJECT OBJECTIVES

Develop an artificial musculature system capable of:

• Protecting hydraulic components
• Distributing mechanical loads
• Reducing vibration
• Improving impact resistance
• Increasing fatigue life
• Supporting modular maintenance
• Integrating with the PI220 hydraulic architecture

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

3. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

The proposed architecture consists of the following layered structure:

1. Protective Outer Skin

2. Abrasion Resistant Layer

3. Energy Absorption Layer

4. Fiber-Reinforced Artificial Muscle

5. Artificial Fascia Reinforcement Mesh

6. Hydraulic Actuator Compartment

7. Carbon Fiber / Titanium Mechanical Skeleton

Each layer performs a dedicated mechanical function.

