10. ENGINEERING CONCLUSIONS

The conceptual investigation indicates that:

• A layered artificial musculature is likely to provide superior performance compared with a single-material approach.

• Fiber-Reinforced Polyurethane Elastomer is a strong candidate for further investigation.

• Artificial Fascia may significantly improve structural stability and load distribution.

• Modular muscle assemblies are expected to simplify maintenance and replacement.

• The overall architecture is suitable for progression toward laboratory prototype development.

The laboratory department is requested to experimentally validate all major assumptions and provide recommendations for future design iterations based upon measured engineering evidence.

